      <title>Running Tests on Deploy with Capistrano</title>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://anarchogeek.com/"&gt;Rabble&lt;/a&gt; just released an article on his &lt;a href="http://blog.testingrails.com"&gt;Testing Rails Blog&lt;/a&gt; on how to &lt;a href="http://blog.testingrails.com/2006/9/4/running-tests-on-deploy-with-capistrano"&gt;run tests on deploy with Capistrano&lt;/a&gt;. It covers basic &lt;a href="http://glu.ttono.us/articles/2006/06/23/capistrano-mike-clark"&gt;Capistrano&lt;/a&gt; tasks that will work with a single deployment server and then goes into some more advanced tasks for multiple server deployment and concurrent deploys. Go check it out.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
